在剧本中，通常会用“'''(annoyed grunt)'''”（生气的咕哝声）来代替这个单词，有几集动画的官方标题中也是如此拼写的。<ref>如此拼写的几集有：“Simpsoncalifragilisticexpiala(Annoyed Grunt)cious”、“E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt)”、“I, (Annoyed Grunt)-Bot”与“G.I. (Annoyed Grunt)”。在标题中包括了“d'oh”一词的几集有：“D'oh-in in the Wind”、“Days of Wine and D'oh'ses”、“C.E. D'oh”、“We're on the Road to D'ohwhere”与“He Loves to Fly and He D'oh's”。</ref>

当霍默的[[配音演员|配音演员]][[丹·卡斯泰拉内塔|丹·卡斯泰拉内塔]]首次被要求用一个声音表达惊呼时，他发出了一串拖长的“doooh”音，他的灵感来自于[[苏格兰|苏格兰]]的大胡子演员[[吉米·芬利森|吉米·芬利森]]<!--Jimmy Finlayson-->，后者曾出演过33部[[劳莱与哈台|劳莱与哈台]]<!--Laurel and Hardy-->的电影，并习惯用“doooh!”这个词语来婉转表示脏话“Damn!”。<ref name=herald>{{Cite news|title=What’s the story with... Homer's D'oh! |trans_title=霍默之D'oh!……的故事 |newspaper=格拉斯哥先驱报 |pages=15 |date=2007-07-21 |url=http://www.theherald.co.uk/search/display.var.1562687.0.whats_the_story_with_homers_doh.php |accessdate=2007-07-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929111111/http://www.theherald.co.uk/search/display.var.1562687.0.whats_the_story_with_homers_doh.php |archivedate=2007-09-29 }}</ref> 节目的创作人[[马特·格勒宁|马特·格勒宁]]觉得这个词再短一些会更适合动画的节奏，于是卡斯泰拉内塔将其缩短为了“D'oh!”<ref name="doh">{{cite news|first=Jeremy|last=Simon|title=Wisdom from The Simpsons' 'D'ohh' boy|format=Interview|publisher=The Daily Northwestern|date=1994-02-11}}</ref>

